Dorsal idiosoma
(
Fig. 1
): Marginal and dorsal shields fused. Dorsal setae basally curved, margins smooth (about 17-23 μm long) (
Figs 2-3
). Surface with small oval pits (
Figs 2-3
).

Legs (
Figs 7-10
). All legs with ambulacral claws and smooth and needle-like setae.
